title: Foster Poultry Farms Recalls Poultry Products Due To Possible Foreign Materials Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, April 29, 2016 Foster Poultry Farms, a Farmerville, La. establishment, is recalling approximately 220,450 pounds of fully cooked frozen chicken nuggets that may be contaminated with extraneous blue plastic and black rubber materials, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS)...
